[00:00.94]MALCOLM	I would the friends we miss were safe arrived.
[00:09.11]SIWARD	Some must go off: and yet, by these I see,
[00:16.35]	So great a day as this is cheaply bought.
[00:23.73]MALCOLM	Macduff is missing, and your noble son.
[00:30.65]ROSS	Your son, my lord, has paid a soldier's debt:
[00:38.35]	He only lived but till he was a man;
[00:44.96]	The which no sooner had his prowess confirm'd
[00:53.13]	In the unshrinking station where he fought,
[01:00.84]	But like a man he died.
[01:05.40]SIWARD	Then he is dead?
[01:08.85]ROSS	Ay, and brought off the field: your cause of sorrow
[01:17.66]	Must not be measured by his worth, for then
[01:25.36]	It hath no end.
[01:28.66]SIWARD	Had he his hurts before?
[01:33.38]ROSS	Ay, on the front.
[01:36.84]SIWARD	Why then, God's soldier be he!
[01:42.34]	Had I as many sons as I have hairs,
[01:48.79]	I would not wish them to a fairer death:
[01:56.02]	And so, his knell is knoll'd.
[02:01.36]MALCOLM	He's worth more sorrow,
[02:05.92]	And that I'll spend for him.
[02:11.27]SIWARD	He's worth no more
[02:15.20]	They say he parted well, and paid his score:
[02:22.90]	And so, God be with him! Here comes newer comfort.
[02:31.39]	[Re-enter MACDUFF, with MACBETH's head]
