[04:17.19]	That fled the snares of watchful tyranny;
[04:24.58]	Producing forth the cruel ministers
[04:31.18]	Of this dead butcher and his fiend-like queen,
[04:39.36]	Who, as 'tis thought, by self and violent hands
[04:47.38]	Took off her life; this, and what needful else
[04:55.40]	That calls upon us, by the grace of Grace,
[05:02.78]	We will perform in measure, time and place:
